This pilot data set was built on previous data standards work conducted by the Cultural Resources Data Sharing Partnership (CRDSP) and the Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC). The National Heritage Solution Pilot was used to populate and test the data standard and provide suggested changes to accommodate the incoming SHPO or BLM State (CA, ID, OR) data. The resource polygon feature class is designed with the intent of importing resource (site) data from each of the participating SHPO's into a standarized format.</abstract><purpose>This aggregated dataset is intended to be used for NEPA, landscape level analyses and project planning purposes. Generally the SHPO's have detailed geographic datasets with related tables. The BLM CRM standard structure is designed to be a simplified version of this data to be used for general planning purposes. Some of the detail of the original data was lost in the process of aggregating it into the BLM CRM data standard. This was done to fit the intended purpose of the dataset. If more detail is needed, the original source data at the SHPO will be available as a reference.</purpose><supplinf>A data migration report is located here: \\blm\dfs\loc\EGIS\OC\Projects\Culture\NationalHeritageSolutionPilot\Documentation\DataMigrationReport</supplinf></descript><timeperd><timeinfo><sngdate><caldate>2016</caldate></sngdate></timeinfo><current>Data was obtained by SHPO's during late 2016 and early 2017.</current></timeperd><status><progress>In work</progress><update>Not determined yet.</update></status><keywords><theme><themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Category</themekt><themekey>society</themekey></theme><theme><themekt>BLM-THEME</themekt><themekey>Anthropology</themekey><themekey>Geospatial</themekey></theme><theme><themekt>BLM-CRM</themekt><themekey>Cultural Resource Management</themekey><themekey>CPPP</themekey><themekey>Colorado Plateau Project Plan</themekey><themekey>NHSP</themekey><themekey>National Heritage Solution Pilot</themekey><themekey>archaeology</themekey></theme><place><placekt>BLM-STATE</placekt><placekey>Alaska</placekey><placekey>Arizona</placekey><placekey>California</placekey><placekey>Colorado</placekey><placekey>Idaho</placekey><placekey>Montana</placekey><placekey>New Mexico</placekey><placekey>Nevada</placekey><placekey>Oregon</placekey><placekey>Utah</placekey><placekey>Wyoming</placekey></place></keywords><accconst>NON-PUBLIC. It may be an individual building, structure, object or site. This pilot data set was built on previous data standards work conducted by the Cultural Resources Data Sharing Partnership (CRDSP) and the Federal Geographic Data Committee (FGDC). The National Heritage Solution Pilot was used to populate and test the data standard and provide suggested changes to accommodate the incoming SHPO or BLM State (CA, ID, OR) data. The resource polygon feature class is designed with the intent of importing resource (site) data from each of the participating SHPO's into a standarized format.</abstract><purpose>This aggregated dataset is intended to be used for NEPA, landscape level analyses and project planning purposes. Generally the SHPO's have detailed geographic datasets with related tables. The BLM CRM standard structure is designed to be a simplified version of this data to be used for general planning purposes. Some of the detail of the original data was lost in the process of aggregating it into the BLM CRM data standard. This was done to fit the intended purpose of the dataset.
